title: Unemployment rate in Canada 2024
summary: In general Unemployment rate has fallen over the Year.
Unemployment rate is roughly constant from 2015 to 2016, and lastly slightly decreasing from 2016 to 2018.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2016 and 2017.
The highest Unemployment rate, of value 6.99 was reached at Year 2016
Minimum Unemployment rate about 5.83 was reached at Year 2018
